Package net.objectzoo.delegates.impl

This package contains support classes that can be used to implement AsyndAction or AsyncFunction delegates.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Action0AsyncSupport
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    Action2AsyncSupport<T1,​T2>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    Action3AsyncSupport<T1,​T2,​T3>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    Action4AsyncSupport<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    ActionAsyncSupport<T>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.
    AsyncExecutor
    This is a helper class that is used for the asynchronous invocation of actions and functions.
    AsyncFutureTask<R>
    This FutureTask subclass is used internally for the asynchronous invocation of actions and funcions and implements the interfaces FunctionAsyncResult and ActionAsyncResult so that it directly serves as return value for the asynchronous invocations and as parameter given to the callback methods.
    Function0AsyncSupport<R>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous functions.
    Function2AsyncSupport<T1,​T2,​R>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous functions.
    Function3AsyncSupport<T1,​T2,​T3,​R>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous functions.
    Function4AsyncSupport<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4,​R>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous functions.
    FunctionAsyncSupport<T,​R>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous functions.
